46:13.689 --> 46:15.255
Cheesecake?

46:19.327 --> 46:21.393
That you?

46:21.395 --> 46:23.762
                      That's me.

46:23.764 --> 46:25.196
Mom, dad?

46:25.198 --> 46:27.498
            Yeah. Connie.
            His name was Angelo.

46:27.500 --> 46:29.266
He's handsome.

46:29.268 --> 46:30.934
                       Yeah.

46:34.806 --> 46:36.071
         My old man was executed

46:36.073 --> 46:38.473
             at Sing Sing in '59

46:38.475 --> 46:42.076
          for murder.

46:42.078 --> 46:43.677
         I was eight.

46:51.219 --> 46:53.419
What happened?

46:53.421 --> 46:54.887
            He was a moving man.

46:54.889 --> 46:56.622
               He used to move
               these rich people

46:56.624 --> 47:00.025
           into mansions
           out in Locust Valley.

47:00.027 --> 47:02.060
       One way or another,
       he got himself into debt.

47:02.062 --> 47:03.261
              I guess
              it was pretty bad,

47:03.263 --> 47:04.895
              because he came up
              with this idea...

47:04.897 --> 47:11.368
           this brilliant,
           idiotic, stupid idea.

47:11.370 --> 47:14.471
             Kidnap a baby
             from a rich family.

47:14.473 --> 47:16.506
            Leave a ransom note.

47:16.508 --> 47:18.574
          They'll pay, no sweat.

47:18.576 --> 47:20.242
         So he kidnaps the baby,

47:20.244 --> 47:22.444
      and while he's waiting for
      the ransom in his car,

47:22.446 --> 47:23.711
        the baby gets tangled up

47:23.713 --> 47:25.045
                in a blanket
                in the back seat

47:25.047 --> 47:27.881
              and he suffocates.

47:27.883 --> 47:30.516
         First time they had
         a murder in Long Beach,

47:30.518 --> 47:33.886
          and it was my old man.

47:33.888 --> 47:36.355
You were
just a little kid then.

47:36.357 --> 47:38.023
It must've been hell.

47:38.025 --> 47:40.392
Yeah. You get through anything
       when you have to,

47:40.394 --> 47:44.495
         but it was...

47:44.497 --> 47:46.096
    anyway, the only thing
       that kept me sane

47:46.098 --> 47:47.931
   was the cop who arrested
          my old man

47:47.933 --> 47:49.198
      kind of adopted me.

47:49.200 --> 47:53.168
       Captain McAuley.
      He was a good guy.

47:56.841 --> 47:59.842
But this...
this the ex-wife?

47:59.844 --> 48:01.376
            Yeah, that's Maggie.

48:01.378 --> 48:04.379
Who's this?

48:04.381 --> 48:07.815
            That's my son, Joey.

48:11.620 --> 48:12.752
You have a son?

48:12.754 --> 48:14.320
                Yeah, I'm sorry.

48:14.322 --> 48:16.088
       I lied to you when I said
       I didn't have any kids.

48:16.090 --> 48:18.223
                      I'm sorry.

48:18.225 --> 48:19.457
    Why did you lie to me,
           Vincent?

48:19.459 --> 48:20.558
                   I don't know.

48:20.560 --> 48:24.628
       I hadn't seen him
        in a long time,

48:24.630 --> 48:26.329
and the divorce was a real mess,

48:26.331 --> 48:28.130
      and Maggie had been
       seeing this guy,

48:28.132 --> 48:34.235
   and, well, I don't know,
           I just...

48:34.237 --> 48:37.972
I lost control of the situation.

48:37.974 --> 48:39.006
What's that mean,
lost control?

48:39.008 --> 48:40.273
What's that, cop talk?

48:40.275 --> 48:41.941
          We used to fight a lot

48:41.943 --> 48:43.976
       with shouting and yelling
       and all that stuff,

48:43.978 --> 48:45.243
      but it never got physical,

48:45.245 --> 48:47.044
                 and then
                 one day it did.

48:47.046 --> 48:51.414
           I lost control, so...

48:51.416 --> 48:55.884
  I, of course, regretted it,
            and...

48:55.886 --> 48:57.985
  but we never got over that.

49:00.622 --> 49:01.687
           On top of everything,

49:01.689 --> 49:02.988
        I think my son
     might've killed a guy

49:02.990 --> 49:04.456
     in a fight over drugs
       the other night.

49:04.458 --> 49:06.491
    What?

49:06.493 --> 49:08.292
            I'm just trying to
            tell you everything.

49:12.264 --> 49:15.865
Yeah, okay, okay.

49:20.637 --> 49:21.636
Why haven't you seen him?

49:21.638 --> 49:24.271
    Well, I tried at first,

49:24.273 --> 49:25.939
          but Maggie
    made it very difficult.

49:25.941 --> 49:27.774
       I could only have
    these supervised visits

49:27.776 --> 49:29.509
     with a social worker
         watching me,

49:29.511 --> 49:30.676
    like I was a criminal.

49:30.678 --> 49:32.878
    It was like I was back
        going to prison

49:32.880 --> 49:35.614
      to see my old man.

49:35.616 --> 49:38.617
      I couldn't take it,
          you know...

49:38.619 --> 49:40.619
So you just
stopped seeing him?

49:40.621 --> 49:42.287
   Well, not just like that.

49:42.289 --> 49:45.623
    I mean, Maggie was also
     doing a number on him

49:45.625 --> 49:48.993
      so he didn't really
     want to be around me,

49:48.995 --> 49:55.265
and I just walked away, I quit.

49:55.267 --> 49:58.968
Maybe I should've tried harder.
         I don't know.

49:58.970 --> 50:04.072
Why couldn't you
tell me this before?

50:04.074 --> 50:06.007
          Well, I...

50:06.009 --> 50:08.743
      I don't know, I...

50:08.745 --> 50:10.077
         That <i> was</i> me.

50:10.079 --> 50:12.746
   With you, it's different.
  It's like I'm the real me.

50:12.748 --> 50:14.347
  I didn't want to ruin that.

50:20.521 --> 50:24.455
              Are you all right?

50:24.457 --> 50:26.890
    Yeah.

50:26.892 --> 50:28.424
It's what I asked for,
isn't it?

50:28.426 --> 50:30.926
             Not so simple, huh?

50:30.928 --> 50:35.930
No. No, it's not.

50:35.932 --> 50:37.631
Vincent,
I'm not your ex-wife.

50:37.633 --> 50:39.866
I'm not going
to judge you.

50:39.868 --> 50:43.202
I never have.
I won't start now.

50:43.204 --> 50:45.270
I've got to think
about this.

50:48.908 --> 50:51.007
I've got to
think about this.

50:53.144 --> 50:55.310
See you, okay?

52:14.924 --> 52:16.924
Gina, I want you to know

52:16.926 --> 52:19.092
   I've got a lot of respect
           for you.

52:19.094 --> 52:21.427
      The way you got your
         shit together

52:21.429 --> 52:22.428
         for your kid.

52:22.430 --> 52:23.896
  I got no problem with you.

52:23.898 --> 52:25.430
Just tell me where Joey is,

52:25.432 --> 52:26.531
and I'll leave you alone.

52:26.533 --> 52:27.532
     I don't know--

52:27.534 --> 52:30.768
Don't!
I don't want to hear it.

52:30.770 --> 52:35.105
I'll tell you what.

52:35.107 --> 52:36.573
I'll give you
till 12:00 noon.

52:36.575 --> 52:37.574
That'll give you
plenty of time

52:37.576 --> 52:39.275
to feed your kid,
take a shower,

52:39.277 --> 52:40.576
do whatever
you got to do.

52:40.578 --> 52:43.812
But after that,
you find Joey, okay?

52:43.814 --> 52:45.280
             Yeah.

52:45.282 --> 52:49.450
                        [CRYING]

52:49.452 --> 52:52.019
   He's a good-looking kid.

53:05.500 --> 53:07.733
                        [BUZZER]

53:11.037 --> 53:12.302
           LaMarca.

53:12.304 --> 53:15.204
         <i> It's Gina. I need</i>
         <i> money to pay the taxi.</i>

53:15.206 --> 53:17.606
          All right,
      I'll be right down.

53:23.146 --> 53:24.378
You okay?

53:24.380 --> 53:25.679
      No. It's 52 bucks.

53:25.681 --> 53:28.181
       Just give him 60.
       He's a nice guy.

53:35.323 --> 53:36.455
                     Who's this?

53:36.457 --> 53:37.722
        Your grandson.

53:44.930 --> 53:47.263
I try not to smoke around him.

53:47.265 --> 53:50.332
            Sometimes it's just,
            you know...

53:50.334 --> 53:53.168
What's his name?

53:53.170 --> 53:55.303
                         Angelo.

53:57.106 --> 53:58.772
                Look, we haven't
                eaten anything.

53:58.774 --> 54:00.673
         You got maybe
         something we could eat?

54:00.675 --> 54:04.175
Yeah, I'll make you
something.

54:05.945 --> 54:08.178
Does Joey help you out?

54:08.180 --> 54:10.880
           He would if he could,
           I guess.

54:10.882 --> 54:12.548
How do you pay your rent?

54:12.550 --> 54:15.083
            I'm on Workfare,
            flipping hamburgers,

54:15.085 --> 54:16.384
           until they figure out

54:16.386 --> 54:17.885
               I've been dipping
               in the register,

54:17.887 --> 54:19.686
            which is going to be
            any day now.

54:19.688 --> 54:22.021
                 Then I'll be
                 totally fucked.

54:22.023 --> 54:23.722
When did you see him
last?

54:23.724 --> 54:24.956
              Night before last.

54:24.958 --> 54:27.825
         He said he was going to
         get some money and go.

54:27.827 --> 54:29.226
Go where?

54:29.228 --> 54:30.894
                  Like he knows?

54:30.896 --> 54:32.896
              Florida, Key West,
              I don't know.

54:32.898 --> 54:34.230
       Whenever he gets rabbity,

54:34.232 --> 54:35.998
          he's going to fly away
          to Florida.

54:36.000 --> 54:37.666
             Like it's
             some magic country,

54:37.668 --> 54:40.735
      when it's the fucking
      dope capital of the world.

54:51.747 --> 54:55.014
   Can I ask you a question
   without you getting mad?

54:55.016 --> 54:56.882
                     Depends.

54:56.884 --> 55:00.451
When you left Joey, was it hard?

55:00.453 --> 55:04.621
                 Very hard.

55:04.623 --> 55:07.090
You miss him?

55:07.092 --> 55:08.758
                  Of course.

55:08.760 --> 55:11.827
        It get easier,
    you know, missing him,

55:11.829 --> 55:12.828
        after a while?

55:12.830 --> 55:14.830
             You just stop
             thinking about it.

55:14.832 --> 55:16.164
               Just lock it out.

55:16.166 --> 55:18.499
             Put your head down,
             just keep walking,

55:18.501 --> 55:20.734
               otherwise it'd be
               too difficult.

55:20.736 --> 55:23.069
    Was it better for Joey,
          you think,

55:23.071 --> 55:25.438
 you know, that you left him?

55:25.440 --> 55:26.572
                    For a while,

55:26.574 --> 55:29.041
                      but I know
          I missed out on stuff.

55:29.043 --> 55:30.208
          Like what?

55:30.210 --> 55:31.676
       Like teaching him
        about things...

55:31.678 --> 55:33.277
    like about good music,

55:33.279 --> 55:36.079
       about old movies,
  not being afraid to fight,

55:36.081 --> 55:38.614
       stuff like that.

55:38.616 --> 55:42.284
  Yeah. I guess what you want
      and what you can do

55:42.286 --> 55:44.352
      is totally different
       things sometimes.

55:44.354 --> 55:48.555
  Gina, I want to help Joey.

55:48.557 --> 55:50.890
      You can't help him.

55:50.892 --> 55:52.791
        You never did.

55:52.793 --> 55:55.960
That's what he says.

56:00.766 --> 56:04.600
Hey, I'm going to go out
to buy some smokes.

56:04.602 --> 56:07.069
Can I borrow
a couple of bucks?

56:07.071 --> 56:10.405
 Yeah, my wallet's in the hall
        on that table.

56:10.407 --> 56:12.840
      You need anything?

56:12.842 --> 56:14.608
                     No, thanks.

56:14.610 --> 56:17.277
    You don't mind watching
       Angelo for a bit?

56:17.279 --> 56:18.811
                  He'll be okay.

56:18.813 --> 56:20.479
   Hey. You be good, honey.

56:20.481 --> 56:22.814
Mommy's going to be
right back, okay?

56:22.816 --> 56:26.951
     His Pampers and stuff
